oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Highlander Fling, Vol. 6, No. 1
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Front page has hand-drawn map of Highlander campus with new buildings and request for support of new building campaign. Highlander's 1945 Resident Program is outlined.

The Highlander Fling was the Highlander Folk School's newsletter. First published in December 1933, the Fling detailed activities and goings-on at Highlander was well as educational programs, articles from staff and participants, and calls to action.
